assume A6: (for i,j being Nat holds ((((1 <= i & i <= m) & 1 <= j) & j <= m) implies ( M2 * (i,j) ) = ( pow (x,( ( i - 1 ) * ( j - 1 ) )) )));
now
let i being Nat,j being Nat;
A7: ( Indices M1 ) = [: ( Seg m ),( Seg m ) :] by MATRIX_1:24;
assume [ i,j ] in ( Indices M1 );
then (ex x,y being set st ((x in ( Seg m ) & y in ( Seg m )) & [ x,y ] = [ i,j ])) by A7,ZFMISC_1:def 2;
then consider z being set,y being set such that A8: [ i,j ] = [ z,y ] and A9: z in ( Seg m ) and A10: y in ( Seg m );
j = ( [ z,y ] `2 ) by A8,MCART_1:def 2
.= y by MCART_1:def 2;
then A11: (1 <= j & j <= m) by A10,FINSEQ_1:1;
i = ( [ z,y ] `1 ) by A8,MCART_1:def 1
.= z by MCART_1:def 1;
then A12: (1 <= i & i <= m) by A9,FINSEQ_1:1;
hence ( M1 * (i,j) ) = ( pow (x,( ( i - 1 ) * ( j - 1 ) )) ) by A5,A11
.= ( M2 * (i,j) ) by A6,A12,A11;
end;
hence thesis by MATRIX_1:27;
